- A product's inventory status is considered 'Low Inventory' when the current inventory quantity falls below the reorder level, and 'Sufficient Inventory' otherwise; 
- The time in the market is calculated as the difference between the dates of the latest and earliest orders for each product; 
- Recent reviews refer to those submitted within the last year.

- "popular items that have left the shelves recently" refers to products ordered within the last month; 
- "restocked" implies products with quantity greater than 0 in the inventory; 
- "price cuts" refers to discounts with a start date on or before today and an end date on or after today, or without an end date.
